					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2135153#post-2753158</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-2135153/scp-2895#post-2753158</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 23 Feb 2017 01:51:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DrArmstrong</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>420092</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I like it, feels like a classic animal scip and the fact that the things it integrates with are filled with rattlesnake venom adds a nice touch of mystery.</p> <p>My only gripe is that I feel the testing log is too short. Granted, you did put in a paragraph stating that it was only initial testing, so I hope you do more, or perhaps an extended testing log as its own page.</p> <p>I'm not gonna lie, I also <em>really</em> want to know exactly what happens when it fuses with a person.</p> <p>That said, this article still feels complete in that I can easily imagine what exactly happens to a person because you described the scip's abilities quite well.</p> <p>+1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
